Kat has a method for finding the difference between two square numbers, $\,a^2 - b^2\,$.
\newline
 \\
Her method is

\begin{center}
	(the sum of $\,a\,$ and $\,b\,$) $\,\times\,$ (the difference between $\,a\,$ and $\,b\,$).
\newline
\end{center}

\noindent \hspace{2.4cm} She shows her method for $\,17^2 - 13^2\,$.
\newline

\begin{center}
	\fbox{
		\begin{minipage}{0.32\textwidth}
			\begin{align*}
				&17^2 - 13^2 \\
				&= (17 + 13) \times (17 - 13) \\
				&= 30 \times 4 \\
				&= 120\\
			\end{align*}
		\end{minipage}
	}
\end{center}

\medskip

\noindent \hspace{2.4cm} Work out $\,29^2 - 21^2\,$ using Kat's method.
